output.prompt='Hello, my name is Jensen Jen-hsun Huang, the CEO of NVIDIA. Could you tell me the futuer of generative AI?'
output.outputs[0].text=" Jensen Huang, the CEO of NVIDIA, is asking about the future of generative AI. Let me break this down into key areas and provide a structured response.\n\n### 1. **Technological Advancements**\n   - **Model Size and Complexity**: Generative models are becoming larger and more complex, with advancements in architectures like Transformers, diffusion models, and neural radiance fields (NeRFs). These models can generate high-resolution images, realistic videos, and even 3D content.\n   - **Efficiency and Accessibility**: There's a growing focus on making these models more efficient, both in terms of computational resources and energy consumption. Techniques like model compression, quantization, and pruning are being developed to make generative AI more accessible on edge devices and mobile platforms.\n   - **Multimodal Capabilities**: Future models will likely be more multimodal, integrating text, images, audio, and video into a single coherent system. This will enable more natural and versatile interactions with AI.\n\n###"
